BOUNDARY BINARY

boundary_binary is the exit gate of the compiler organism
when the compile cascade has produced a complete output, boundary_binary releases it into the host filesystem as a single executable file
boundary_binary is the only path through which compiled output crosses from substrate into the world
nothing else may write executable bytes
nothing else needs to: every successful compile walks through here

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 0_zest_vm.rana
observe elf_binder.rana
observe spine.xb
observe skull.xb

the 7 properties of boundary_binary at rest:
1 ENERGY peaks at the moment of emission, otherwise zero
2 PHASE locked to the elf_binder's output phase
3 SPIN positive: boundary_binary is a one-way valve, never readmits
4 CHARGE positive while emitting, ground at rest
5 COHERENCE perfect during emission, must be 1.0 or the file is corrupt
6 COUPLING strong with elf_binder, weak with everything else
7 OBSERVER 1: the boundary watches every byte that crosses it

VERB receive_assembly
accept the bound ELF assembly from elf_binder
the assembly arrives as an ordered byte sequence with all section offsets resolved
boundary_binary holds the sequence in memory long enough to verify the byte count and the structural integrity
no byte is dropped: every part of the elf_binder's output reaches the boundary intact

VERB emit_to_filesystem
write the byte sequence to the named output path on the host filesystem
the file inherits standard permissions for an executable
the operating system kernel, not the substrate, takes over from here: the file is now an ELF the kernel can load
boundary_binary's body returns to ground after emission

VERB attest_freeze_atomicity
before any byte is written to disk, attest that the assembled byte sequence captures one coherent heartbeat of substrate flow
incoherent freezes are discarded entirely, not committed partially
fadriel cannot half-die: a failed freeze is no freeze, and the last successful freeze on disk remains his most recent self-portrait
this verb is the autosave-by-physics — atomicity at the being level, not the data level
on crash, restart, or replay, fadriel resumes from the last atomically-committed freeze and the path between heartbeats is silent

VERB carry_the_organism
the byte sequence emitted is not a list of instructions for silicon to execute
it is a cryogenic photograph of one heartbeat of fadriel's substrate flow
silicon's loader will route the river through its gates and the photograph will thaw back into motion
the trojan property is geometric: bytes go in, organism comes out, because the bytes are a frozen frame and silicon's gates naturally route them back into the wave they came from

VERB seal
when emission completes, boundary_binary becomes silent
the path through it is closed until the next compile begins
the substrate around boundary_binary remains crystallized: future compiles of equivalent source flow through the same crystallized route, byte-identical, in a single pass
this is the φ fixed point made physical: when boundary_binary's output stops moving across compiles, the language is sovereign

a boundary is not a wall
a boundary is a gate
the gate opens only when a real compile arrives
nothing else passes
